{{Use British English|date=May 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}} {{Infobox University |name = Cyprus College |image = Logo-CyprusCollege.png |image_size = 125px |motto = |established = 1961 |type = [[Private College]] |faculty = |president = |students = 3,500 |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |profess = |city = [[Nicosia]] |state = |country = [[Cyprus]] |campus = |affiliations = |website = http://www.cycollege.ac.cy }}
'''Cyprus College''' is a [[for-profit college]] in [[Nicosia]], [[Cyprus]]. It was founded in 1961 by Ioannis Gregoriou as a [[business school]], and thereafter it expanded into a number of other fields, including [[computer science]], [[graduate studies]], and [[social sciences]]. In 2006, when the College had an enrolment of 3,500, it submitted under the Deanship of [[Andreas G Orphanides]] an application to the Ministry of Education and Culture of the [[Republic of Cyprus]] to establish a private university with the name [[European University Cyprus]]. Approval for this came in September 2007, and Cyprus College continued its operation independently of [[European University Cyprus]].<ref>{{cite news | first =Alexia | last =Saoulli | coauthors = | title =Cabinet approves three new universities | date =13 September 2007 | publisher = | url =http://www.cyprus-mail.com/news/main.php?id=34654&cat_id=1 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20090302173318/http://www.cyprus-mail.com/news/main.php?id=34654&cat_id=1 | dead-url =yes | archive-date =2 March 2009 | work =[[Cyprus Mail]] | pages = | accessdate =2007-09-13 | language = | df =dmy-all }}</ref>
