The '''UNESCO Center of Peace'''
is a [[Non-profit organization]] founded in 2004 in Maryland USA. It promotes the ideals of [[United Nations|the United Nations]] Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization ([[UNESCO]]).

UNESCO Center for Peace is partner to [[Frederick County Public Schools (Maryland)|Frederick County Public Schools]], [[Hood College]], Frederick Community College, [[Maryland School for the Deaf]] (MSD) on a variety of community projects that include various after school programs, Distinguished Speaker Series, Regional [[Model United Nations]], International Model United Nations, Celebrations and Commemorations of major United Nations International Days, the Frederick Stamp Festival, National and International Exchange Programs for High School and College level students and schools

